{"section_number":"VI-18","section_id":"134","structure_id":"24","catch_line":"Water, sanitary wastewater, and stormwater utilities.","history":"","full_text":" (a)  To be separate enterprises.\n\n(1)Water, sanitary wastewater, and stormwater utilities each shall be conducted as a separate\nenterprise.\n\n(2)Each of the utilities shall be financially self-sustaining and shall be operated without profit\nor loss to the other funds or programs of the City.\n\n (b)  Utility budgets; agency budget estimates.\n\n(1)Separate budgets, which shall include estimates of revenue and expense for the ensuing fiscal\nyear, shall be prepared annually for the water, sanitary wastewater, and stormwater utilities.  \nThe actions of the Board of Estimates and the City Council on the utilities\u2019 budgets are\nsubject to this section.\n\n(2)The budget estimates of each agency of the City shall include items for the use of services\nprovided by the water, sanitary wastewater, and stormwater utilities, as applicable.\n\n (c)  Interfund and other borrowing.\n\nNothing in this section prevents the following, if otherwise in accordance with law:\n\n   (1)interfund cash borrowings between the water, sanitary wastewater, and stormwater\nutilities to meet temporary cash requirements; or \n\n   (2)borrowings by these utilities from the General Fund or any other fund of the City.\n\n (d)  Transfer of employees. \n\n  Nothing in this section prevents:\n\n   (1)the transfer or assignment of employees from one utility to another utility or to any\ndepartment, board, commission, or agency of the City; or\n\n   (2)the division of employees\u2019 time among the utilities or between a utility and any\ndepartment, board, commission, or agency of the City.\n\n (e)  Supplemental legislation.\n\nThe Mayor and City Council may enact, from time to time, ordinances not inconsistent with this\nCharter, as necessary or desirable to implement the provisions of this section.\n(Res. 12-004, ratified Nov. 6, 2012.)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n{Page Intentionally Left Blank}\r\r","ancestry":{"1":{"id":"24","name":"Board of Estimates","identifier":"VI","label":"article","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI\/"}},"structure_contents":{"0":{"id":"125","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-1","catch_line":"Establishment and organization.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-1\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-1\/"},"1":{"id":"135","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-2","catch_line":"Powers and duties.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-2\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-2\/"},"2":{"id":"136","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-3","catch_line":"Fiscal year; budget schedule.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-3\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-3\/"},"3":{"id":"137","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-4","catch_line":"Assistance from Finance Director and Planning Commission.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-4\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-4\/"},"4":{"id":"138","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-5","catch_line":"Preparation of proposed Ordinance of Estimates.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-5\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-5\/"},"5":{"id":"139","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-6","catch_line":"Adoption of proposed Ordinance of Estimates.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-6\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-6\/"},"6":{"id":"140","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-7","catch_line":"Enactment of Ordinance of Estimates.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-7\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-7\/"},"7":{"id":"141","structure_id":"24","section_number":"VI-8","catch_line":"Deficiencies; supplementary appropriations.","url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/VI-8\/","api_url":"http:\/\/charter.baltimorecode\/api\/law\/VI-8\/"},